1. Finance is the study of value.

2. Value creation has two components - Time and Uncertainity.

3. Study of Finance helps in making better decisions in all walks of life.

4. This course has two components - Valuation and Investing.

5. REAL ASSETS: Something that produces a commodity product or a service that can be sold.

6. Liabilities come in the form of debt and equity.

7. The course is all about valuation of real assets and the investment in them through debt and equity.

8. Following three important assumptions have been made during the course:

	a. Competitive markets.

	b. Capital can flow easily.

	c. Frictions are small relative to to the power of good idea. 